<HEADLINE>
NEW POSTAL RULE REQUIRES `TRUTH' IN P.O. ADDRESSES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ A little-noticed U.S. Postal Service rule meant to
cut fraud has mail box renters steamed and owners of mail box
outlets worried about their livelihood.
</P>
<P>
   The rule is aimed at people and companies that use swank
addresses for what are actually pigeon holes at places like Mail
Boxes Etc. The new guideline requires renters of such boxes to
strike the potentially misleading ``suite,'' ``office,'' ``bureau''
or ``unit no.'' from their address in favor of ``PMB,''
postal-speak for a private mail box.
</P>
<P>
   For the next few months, the postal service will deliver mail to
private mail boxes, regardless of designation. But come November,
letters and packages addressed to a rented mailbox with anything
but the PMB designation will be returned to sender, even when the
post office knows the intended recipient.
</P>
<P>
   ``What's the point of having a rule if you don't enforce it?''
said Terri Bouffiou, Southern California spokeswoman for the U.S.
Postal Service.
</P>
<P>
   The new policy, which was made public March 25 in a Federal
Register announcement, is meant to cut down on mail fraud. Too
often, postal officials say, criminals use mail boxes with
impressive addresses as a front for money-bilking operations.
</P>
<P>
   ``Many, many of our criminal investigations lead to the use of a
(private mail box),'' said Pamela Prince, a postal inspector in
Pasadena. ``When we go to obtain a copy of the application, we find
a fictitious name may have been used, fictitious identification and
even a fictitious address. Or sometimes a real address is listed
and we find out it's yet another mail box.''
</P>
<P>
   For that reason, Prince said, the Postal Service issupermarkets,
upscale grocers and other places will dramatically increase the
company's business.
</P>
<P>
   Cheesecake als won a large order from a major restaurant chain
that Gordon declined to identify. Shipments will start this
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Both deals have the potential of adding millions to annual
sales, company officials said.!dlim!
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
