<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW COACH SCHMID TO OBSERVE GALAXY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA _ New Galaxy coach Sigi Schmid will be an observer
tonight as the team plays host to San Jose at the Rose Bowl at
7:30.
</P>
<P>
   Schmid, hired after the team fired Octavio Zambrano on
Wednesday, said assistant coach Ralph Perez will control the Galaxy
tonight. Schmid said he will assume full control of the team
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy (2-3) is in fifth place in the Western Conference,
has lost three straight and has scored only three goals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to observe,'' Schmid said. ``I have to use my ears and
my eyes and I have to watch and listen and sense what's going on.''
</P>
<P>
   Schmid, hired after a sensational 20-year run at UCLA that
included three national titles, said he needs time to evaluate the
team's individual talent.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every coach always looks at things a little bit differently,''
Schmid said. ``There are lots of different ways to be successful.
There are teams who win World Cups one way and teams who win World
Cups a completely different way. From that standpoint, I have to
see what's out there.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are certain players that may catch my eye more than they
caught Octavio's eye and vice versa. That's not to say one's right
and one's wrong, it's just an assemblage of preference. It's like
one guy likes chocolate and the other vanilla. I don't know what's
going to happen down the line, but I can promise we will be about
winning games.''
</P>
<P>
   Schmid has been a regular at Galaxy games the past four seasons.
Six of his former players are on the Galaxy's roster, including
goalkeeper Kevin Hartman, who welcomed his former coach's arrival.
</P>
<P>
   ``What Sigi does is develop a technical base with the players,''
Hartman said. ``If you notice, most UCLA players have good
technical ability but more than anything they recognize
opportunities to go forward as quickly as possible to put people
under pressure and develop counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's always been Sigi's style. He likes to develop the
attacks down the wings with speedy outside midfielders and likes to
have people who are going to finish opportunities in the box.''
</P>
<P>
   Ironically, Schmid's Bruin teams scrimmaged the Galaxy on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``For me, the only thing I can see at this point was their
directness of play at certain times,'' Schmid said of the Galaxy.
``And that's not saying you're only going to counter-attack or
you're only going to go over the top. The object of the game is to
get behind the defense and you have to do that in a timely
manner.''
</P>
<P>
   Although Zambrano was fired after only five games, Schmid says
he is not expecting a quick fix.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want people to know this could take some time,'' he said.
``I hope people don't only judge me on my first 10 games. I know my
coaching style. I sometimes tend to be a nag. I get in people's
ears, but I also get players to do what I want them to do
eventually. It might be easier because some guys know me, but from
week to week you will see a better team.''
</P>
</TEXT>
