<HEADLINE>
`GOURMET' RANKS PHOENIX-AREA RESORTS AMONG WORLD'S TOP 10 HOTELS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PETER CORBETT  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _  &UR; (EDITORS: LIST OF HOTELS AT END OF STORY) Two
Phoenix-area resorts _ the Boulders and the Phoenician _ were
ranked among the world's top 10 hotels in a ``Gourmet'' magazine
survey that named the Halekulani in Honolulu as the best.
</P>
<P>
   The Boulders in Carefree was seventh and the Phoenician ninth in
``Gourmet's''Rooms at the Top survey published in the May issue,
which hits newsstands Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're very pleased,'' said Steve Sampson, Boulders director of
sales and marketing. ``The awards and accolades that come to the
Boulders are spectacular and we consider this a worthy accolade.''
</P>
<P>
   The Boulders is ranked No. 1 in the Southwest, just ahead of the
Phoenician. Arizona Biltmore is fourth and Marriott's Camelback Inn
is fifth in the Southwest.
</P>
<P>
   Consistent service by a stable staff along with the quality of
the restaurants, rooms and golf are why people keep coming back to
the 15-year-old Boulders and why ``Gourmet'' readers rated it so
high, Sampson said.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenician spokeswoman Sally Cooper said the rankings are
important because they come from guests who have stayed at the
resort. The high marks from the magazine's readers validate the
staff's efforts to maintain high standards, she added.
</P>
<P>
   This is the third year for the hotel survey, said Karen Larkin,
a spokeswoman for ``Gourmet,'' a Conde Nast magazine with a
circulation of about 850,000.
</P>
<P>
   The Phoenician was ranked sixth worldwide last year and 17th in
1997. The Boulders was ranked one of the top Southwest hotels the
previous two years.
</P>
<P>
   In this year's survey, more than 150 hotels, resorts and inns in
27 countries were ranked.
</P>
<P>
   Readers also determined their preferred hotels for
special-interest travel.
</P>
<P>
   Disney's Grand Floridian Resort &AMP; Spa was ranked the best family
resort. The Regent in Hong Kong was cited as the best business
hotel and for romance, readers preferred the Ritz-Carlton Laguna
Niguel in Dana Point, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   The Hotel Ritz in Paris has the top-rated pool. Readers chose
Ashford Castle in County Mayo, Ireland, as the best in design and
architecture. &QL; 
Peter Corbett can be reached at (602) 444-4815 or at
peter.corbett(at)pni.com via e-mail.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
`GOURMET' RANKINGS IN WORLD, SOUTHWEST &QL; 
These are the world's top 10 hotels as ranked by readers of
``Gourmet'' magazine:
</P>
<P>
   1. Halekulani, Honolulu.
</P>
<P>
   2. The Oriental, Bangkok, Thailand.
</P>
<P>
   3. Villa D'Este, Cernobbio, Italy.
</P>
<P>
   4. The Regent, Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
   5. Hotel Ritz, Paris.
</P>
<P>
   6. Ritz-Carlton, Naples, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   7. The Boulders, Carefree.
</P>
<P>
   8. The Greenbrier, White Sulphur Springs, W.Va.
</P>
<P>
   9. The Phoenician, Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   10. Four Seasons Resort, Nevis, West Indies. &QL; 
These are the top hotels in the SOUTHWEST, according to ``Gourmet''
readers: &QL; 
1. The Boulders.
</P>
<P>
   2. The Phoenician.
</P>
