<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-HORNETS (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on
the Knicks-Hornets, a game key to each of their playoff hopes. By
William C. Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-DIMAGGIO-MEMORIAL (New York) _ Who but Joe DiMaggio could
draw a swath of New Yorkers to St. Patrick's Cathedral that
included Henry Kissinger, Phil Rizzuto, Joe Piscopo, Warner Wolf,
E.L Doctorow, Tim McCarver, Mort Zuckerman, Frank Petrizzo and Jim
McGonigle? On Friday, on the insistence of friends who thought a
hero deserved a hero's tribute, the reclusive Yankee Clipper was
celebrated in the most public of ways. By Jane Gross.
</P>
<P>
   HORSE-BUZZER (Louisville, Ky.) _ When Valhol captured the
Arkansas Derby in a huge upset two weekends ago, most people in the
racing world were willing accept his victory as one of the
unpredictable results that makes the sport interesting. But now the
question is whether the jockey on Valhol used an illegal electric
buzzer to make the horse run faster. The jockey denies he did, and
various racing authorities are investigating. But the case has put
a spotlight on a long and sordid history of jockeys indeed using
buzzers on horses. By Joe Drape.
</P>
