<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC RESERVES STAND OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC concluded its spring practice Friday with a
36-play scrimmage highlighted by the play of the Trojans' reserves.
</P>
<P>
   Junior quarterback Mike Van Raaphorst completed 6 of 7 passes
for 65 yards and one touchdown _ a 24-yard scoring pass to walk-on
Matt Nickels.
</P>
<P>
   Carson Palmer completed 1 of 4 passes for 6 yards. Sophomore
tailback Frank Strong was the leading rusher with 36 yards in six
carries.
</P>
<P>
   ``We got the young guys one more shot at it,'' USC coach Paul
Hackett said. ``There's been great enthusiasm this spring. We've
got some holes, no question about it, but we'll fill them when new
guys come in.''
</P>
<P>
   Free safety Darnell Lacy, linebacker Sultan Abdul-Malik,
defensive end Lonnie Ford and walk-on strong safety John Morgan led
the defense with three tackles.
</P>
<P>
   ``The No. 1 focus that needs to be accomplished is the
rebuilding of the premier defense in the Pac-10,'' Hackett said.
``I think we made those strides in the spring, particularly in the
defensive line.''
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver R. Jay Soward and linebacker Jason Steen did not
participate to concentrate on academics.
</P>
<P>
   USC will return to practice Aug. 9, when its freshmen report to
campus. Returning players report Aug. 12 and the Trojans hold their
first practice at UC Irvine on Aug. 13. They will practice two
weeks in Irvine before returning for a final week at USC.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
