   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ People are mourning 168 Los
Angeles police officers. No, they didn't die. They've all been
transfered back to patrol units after serving long stints as senior
lead officers dealing one-on-one with people in their communities.
By Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
