building was on his paper route, he said he knew none of the
victims.
</P>
<P>
   Charles Starkweather was 19 in 1958 when he led Caril Fugate,
14, on a weeklong killing spree across Nebraska and Wyoming in
which 11 people were shot, stabbed and strangled to death. Miss
