<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-PENGUINS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ Pittsburgh at New
Jersey, Game 2, 2 p.m. By Alex Yannis.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of the Times column on Mia
Hamm of the U.S. women's soccer team, which plays China on Sunday.
She has been held scoreless for the past six games, but says it's
no big deal. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-CRASH-SURVIVOR (Somerset, Ky.) _ The last time some 60,000
people saw Jason Watts, most of them were cheering lustily for him
and his University of Kentucky football team. Last Tuesday
afternoon, the day after his 22nd birthday, Watts shuffled into the
Pulaski County Courthouse here, his walk impeded because his ankles
were chained. Three weeks before, Watts had pleaded guilty to two
counts of reckless homicide and asked to begin his jail term
immediately. His celebration with friends had turned tragic. By Ira
Berkow.
</P>
