   NATO-SUMMIT (Washington) _ NATO leaders consider ways to halt
oil shipments to Yugoslavia, including plans to stop and search
vessels suspected of carrying the fuel. The leaders also appear set
to approve a ``strategic concept'' for handling future threats to
the alliance such as regional conflicts, terrorism and
proliferation of weapons of mass destruction. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
