<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: MOSES COMMANDS: HUNKER IN THE BUNKER 
 (DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By MAUREEN DOWD   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ This is the actual text of a letter sent Thursday
to the NRA's members by its president, Charlton Heston. We offer
simultaneous captioning, in parenthesis, conveying what Heston must
really think.
</P>
<P>
   Dear NRA Member:
</P>
<P>
   We are writing to ask for your patience, your prayers, and your
presence.
</P>
<P>
   (We're in the crosshairs again, men. The p.c. libs like Rosie
O'Donnell are yelping. Every time some teen-age loser who couldn't
make the football team or date the cheerleader abuses our
pump-action, sawed-off product line, we catch hell. But the
networks will get bored with Columbine. Oklahoma City and Jonesboro
passed. All we need to do is hunker in the bunker.)
</P>
<P>
   We had long looked forward to the 1999 Denver meeting and
exhibitions as a time to conduct necessary NRA business, enjoy your
fellowship, express our unity and celebrate our precious freedoms.
But the tragedy in Littleton last Tuesday calls upon us to take
steps, along with dozens of other planned public events, to modify
our schedule to show our profound sympathy and respect for the
families and communities in the Denver area in their time of great
loss.
</P>
<P>
   (All Columbine needed was armed guards and a more conservative
dress code. No black trench coats, just beige Burberrys. As Jesse
Ventura said, if only the concealed weapons law had passed in
Colorado, students and teachers secretly packing heat could have
cut down those two outcasts. The problem is not that bad guys have
guns; it's that good guys don't.)
</P>
<P>
   For that reason, we have canceled the Exhibit Hall Exposition
and all other seminars, luncheons and festive ceremonies normally
associated with our annual gathering.
</P>
<P>
   (Dagnabit. We know how much you fine citizens love to fondle
those M-2 Carbines and Ruger Redhawks. And the ladies will miss
checking out the ultimate fashion accessory: the ``feminine
protection handbag'' for concealing a pistol.
</P>
<P>
   But we just have to lie low while Clinton and all those bearded
TV shrinks offer psychobabble about healing. Then we resume our ads
instructing America's youth on their right to own a handgun, a long
gun, a black gun, a purple gun, a pretty gun, an ugly gun. There's
nothing like a gun to give a lonely guy a little confidence, to
make him feel the lifeblood of liberty coursing through his veins.)
</P>
<P>
   Instead, we will only conduct the Annual Meeting of Members at
10 a.m. on Saturday, May 1, in the Colorado Convention Center, as
required by New York not-for-profit statutes which govern our
Bylaws. Saturday night's member's Reception with Oklahoma
Representative J.C. Watts will also remain scheduled.
</P>
<P>
   (Too bad Watts chickened out after we sent the letter. Hey,
let's invite Dan Quayle. As Dan said so profoundly after Littleton:
``Do you really believe that if we had stricter gun control laws in
the state of Colorado that this accident, this tragedy, would not
have happened? . . . So, I hope we don't try to use this as an
excuse to go and take away guns. Let's focus on behavior.'')
</P>
<P>
   Our spirits must endure this terrible suffering together, and so
must the freedoms that bring us together. We must stand in somber
but unshakable unity, even in this time of anguish.
</P>
<P>
   (Just blame Marilyn Manson, Oliver Stone, the Internet, video
games, Magic cards, Goths. Here's a good sound bite: Software makes
people go nuts, not hardware. Guns don't kill people; trench coats
kill people. Guns don't kill people; people who have not reached
closure with their anger kill people.)
</P>
<P>
   That's why we need you, more than ever, to attend this
gathering. Each of us, Charlton Heston and Wayne LaPierre, will
make a major address on the crisis all Americans now face, and we
will do all we can to help your voice be heard.
</P>
<P>
   (Clinton won't be a problem. He sounded so limp, talking about
teaching kids to ``express their anger and to resolve their
conflicts with words, not weapons.'' The wimpy Democrats are still
scared because we wacked 'em in '94. We'll rev up Bob Barr and the
other pols we own.)
</P>
<P>
   In light of these changes we ask you to give us your patience,
to give the families of Littleton your prayers, and to give freedom
your presence at 10 a.m. Saturday morning, May 1.
</P>
<P>
   (Denver can't keep us out. We paid for this microphone. Lock and
load!)(BOX)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
