<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, April 25. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
SCHOOL SHOOTING (Phoenix) _ `The sleep of reason produces
monsters,'' observed the Spanish painter Francisco de Goya. The
monsters who slaughtered more than a dozen classmates and teachers
in Littleton, Colo., were the products of a culture in which reason
has been comatose for a very long time. The killers were raised in
a society in which rules and standards are in such constant flux as
to be non-existent. Morals are a matter of spin, values a matter of
choice, and violence is glorified in movies and music. Yet we read
things such as this in a news story: ``Authorities may never know
what sent two young men on a shooting spree at Columbine High
School.'' Maybe authorities will never know. But you do. By KENNETH
LAFAVE. Story will move in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
